00:14:36.530 --> 00:14:41.610
And 45% claim they
get more opportunities

00:14:41.610 --> 00:14:44.860
by using LinkedIn as well.

00:14:44.860 --> 00:14:47.950
And here's five reasons
why top social sellers

00:14:47.950 --> 00:14:49.590
are leveraging social.

00:14:49.590 --> 00:14:53.200
One is that it opens
doors to other areas.

00:14:53.200 --> 00:14:56.320
So other lines of business
that you may be interested in,

00:14:56.320 --> 00:14:59.570
LinkedIn opens the doors.

00:14:59.570 --> 00:15:03.850
In the old world of
branding that I talked about

00:15:03.850 --> 00:15:06.300
with Barbara Corcoran, it
was very hard to get it.

00:15:06.300 --> 00:15:08.040
You had to be a
very clever person,

00:15:08.040 --> 00:15:10.580
like she was, to
get media attention.

00:15:10.580 --> 00:15:13.100
Today LinkedIn
gives you a platform

00:15:13.100 --> 00:15:16.240
to build your brand
on the profile.

00:15:16.240 --> 00:15:19.180
Also it's the modern
way of doing business.

00:15:19.180 --> 00:15:23.420
A lot of tech sellers tell
me that the smaller clients

00:15:23.420 --> 00:15:26.710
that they're going after, after
they meet, even with the CEO,

00:15:26.710 --> 00:15:31.310
they'll get an email wanting
to connect on LinkedIn.

00:15:31.310 --> 00:15:35.380
So it's really kind of a
modern way of doing business.

00:15:35.380 --> 00:15:40.620
And it really paves the way
to the C-suite and the things

00:15:40.620 --> 00:15:42.390
that you really want to do.

00:15:42.390 --> 00:15:45.810
And a lot of top
social sellers really

00:15:45.810 --> 00:15:49.590
claim that it helps them not
only build their prospect pool

00:15:49.590 --> 00:15:52.340
but also shorten the sales time.

00:15:52.340 --> 00:15:56.990
So what is social selling
and how do you do it?

00:15:56.990 --> 00:15:59.990
Four components of social
selling, number one is brand.

00:15:59.990 --> 00:16:01.910
You want to build your brand.

00:16:01.910 --> 00:16:04.340
Number two is you want
to find the right people,

00:16:04.340 --> 00:16:07.100
you want to engage
them, and then

00:16:07.100 --> 00:16:09.252
you want to build
relationships with them.

00:16:09.252 --> 00:16:10.210
So let's break it down.

00:16:10.210 --> 00:16:13.790
Let's look at step one,
building your personal brand.

00:16:16.390 --> 00:16:20.660
An important thing to realize
is a weak online footprint

00:16:20.660 --> 00:16:22.160
says you're a weak brand.

00:16:22.160 --> 00:16:26.142
When people look at your
profile and not much is there,

00:16:26.142 --> 00:16:29.370
they're going to make the
assumption that you're not

00:16:29.370 --> 00:16:34.100
as strong as someone that has
a strong profile that utilizes

00:16:34.100 --> 00:16:37.140
the 2,000 characters in
the summary, that tells

00:16:37.140 --> 00:16:40.370
an interesting story, that has
a lot of activities going on.

00:16:40.370 --> 00:16:41.880
So it's a key thing
you want to do.

00:16:41.880 --> 00:16:46.650
And also pull strategies
where clients and prospects

00:16:46.650 --> 00:16:50.740
are attracted to you really
require a strong brand.

00:16:50.740 --> 00:16:52.700
They're not going to
go to a brand that

00:16:52.700 --> 00:16:54.690
doesn't look like
it's substantial.

00:16:54.690 --> 00:16:56.670
That's true in
the product world.

00:16:56.670 --> 00:17:00.690
It's also true in the
world of personal branding.

00:17:00.690 --> 00:17:03.950
So how do you figure
out what your brand is,

00:17:03.950 --> 00:17:06.510
and how do you figure out
how to build your brand?

00:17:06.510 --> 00:17:08.609
In the marketing
world, the first step

00:17:08.609 --> 00:17:10.730
is we do a brand audit.

00:17:10.730 --> 00:17:14.390
And part of the brand audit
is doing a SWOT analysis,

00:17:14.390 --> 00:17:17.394
looking at your strengths
and your weaknesses.

00:17:19.960 --> 00:17:21.880
The neat thing about
the SWOT analysis

00:17:21.880 --> 00:17:24.579
is it forces you to
look at the marketplace.

00:17:24.579 --> 00:17:28.410
What are the opportunities
in the marketplace?

00:17:28.410 --> 00:17:29.360
And what's changing?

00:17:29.360 --> 00:17:30.700
What are the threats?

00:17:30.700 --> 00:17:32.780
What should I be worried about?

00:17:32.780 --> 00:17:34.170
And when you do
the SWOT and when

00:17:34.170 --> 00:17:38.080
you think of your strengths, you
want to frame your strengths.

00:17:38.080 --> 00:17:43.020
So that strength, how is
that demonstrated in things

00:17:43.020 --> 00:17:46.600
that I've accomplished
in my career?

00:17:46.600 --> 00:17:48.870
You want to demonstrate it.

00:17:48.870 --> 00:17:51.540
Because of this
trait, I accomplished

00:17:51.540 --> 00:17:54.540
x relative to others.

00:17:54.540 --> 00:17:56.160
So you really want
to frame it so

00:17:56.160 --> 00:17:59.420
that people can understand it.

00:17:59.420 --> 00:18:01.750
A big thing we do
in the brand audit

00:18:01.750 --> 00:18:04.530
also is look at the competition.

00:18:04.530 --> 00:18:06.260
Who are our competition?

00:18:06.260 --> 00:18:08.040
What is their sales message?

00:18:08.040 --> 00:18:09.520
What are their tactics?

00:18:09.520 --> 00:18:11.430
So you really want to
have a gauge of what

00:18:11.430 --> 00:18:13.820
your competitors
are doing as well.

00:18:13.820 --> 00:18:18.450
And what it's all leading up
to is defining your value.

00:18:18.450 --> 00:18:22.400
What is your unique
selling proposition?

00:18:22.400 --> 00:18:24.320
And what you try to
do in all of this

00:18:24.320 --> 00:18:26.830
is you're looking for
your differentiator.

00:18:26.830 --> 00:18:29.940
What's different about your
brand compared to others?

00:18:29.940 --> 00:18:33.100
And you want to be able
to answer these questions.

00:18:33.100 --> 00:18:36.110
What qualities make you
different, even better

00:18:36.110 --> 00:18:38.520
than others?

00:18:38.520 --> 00:18:43.020
Unlike others in my field,
I-- fill in the blank.

00:18:43.020 --> 00:18:46.660
The value you bring to a
business situation is x.

00:18:46.660 --> 00:18:48.350
So let's just take
a couple of minutes.

00:18:48.350 --> 00:18:51.630
I'd like everyone to pair up
with the person next to them

00:18:51.630 --> 00:18:55.190
and answer these questions,
just whatever comes to mind.

00:18:55.190 --> 00:18:57.907
You really want to be able
to own your value in terms

00:18:57.907 --> 00:18:58.740
of building a brand.

00:18:58.740 --> 00:19:02.060
So let's just take a few
minutes, each partner, and just

00:19:02.060 --> 00:19:06.360
brainstorm with each other
and answer these questions.

00:19:06.360 --> 00:19:09.490
Can I get some sharing?

00:19:09.490 --> 00:19:12.340
What qualities
make you different?

00:19:12.340 --> 00:19:16.330
This is the word that
worries people, even better

00:19:16.330 --> 00:19:17.600
than other people.

00:19:17.600 --> 00:19:20.574
Anyone willing to share what
qualities make you different?

